<p>The <a href="https://www.leverhulme.ac.uk/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Leverhulme Trust</a> has announced the winners of its 2025 Major Research Fellowships, and three philosophy professors are among them.<span id="more-56233"></span></p>
<p>They are:</p>
<ul>
<li><a href="https://christoph-kelp.com/index.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Christoph Kelp</a> (University of Glasgow), awarded £169,830 for <em>Norms of Inquiry</em></li>
<li><a href="https://www.stephenlaurence.net/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Stephen Laurence</a> (University of Sheffield), awarded £196,933 for <em>Beyond Words: Concepts in Humans and (Other) Animals</em></li>
<li><a href="http://www.emichaelson.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Eliot Michaelson</a> (King’s College London), awarded £192,518 for <em>Meaning and Dissembling  </em></li>
</ul>
<div id="attachment_56235" style="width: 717px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-56235" class="size-full wp-image-56235" src="https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/leverhulme-major-research-philosophers-2025.png" alt="" width="707" height="295" srcset="https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/leverhulme-major-research-philosophers-2025.png 707w, https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/leverhulme-major-research-philosophers-2025-300x125.png 300w, https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/leverhulme-major-research-philosophers-2025-400x167.png 400w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 707px) 100vw, 707px" /><p id="caption-attachment-56235" class="wp-caption-text">Christoph Kelp, Stephen Laurence, and Eliot Michaelson</p></div>
<p>Twenty-seven fellowships were awarded in total. You can view the complete list of them <a href="https://www.leverhulme.ac.uk/listings?field_grant_scheme_target_id=11" target="_blank" rel="noopener">here</a>.</p>
